The paper discusses a neural network model for learning-induced categorical perception, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the compression and expansion of distances in hidden-unit space, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions language and learning as potential causes of categorical perception, which could place it in the sub-categories of Computation and Language (cs.CL) and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
